{
  "stem": "93.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And as we were knocking the tanks out, they were bringing crews in and bringing tanks off the assembly line and attacking us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But in any event, in about 10 days of fighting, we forced the Germans to surrender.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we were in the process of mopping up the city, and my colonel sent me through to make a reconnaissance to find a place where we could put the regiment for that night.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And this was my first actual encounter with victims of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "What happened is, as I was driving through-- and this was in the afternoon sometime, sometime in April of 1945-- I noticed a group of people standing that were dressed in these black and white uniforms.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I stopped my jeep and walked up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And there was a German SS officer, I thought, or else a policeman, whatever, all dressed up.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "His boots were immaculately polished, and he was perspiring profusely, which is very unusual, because April is quite chilly in Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I walked into the building, and when I got in there, the sight that greeted me was my first view of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "This was a building that was perhaps-- the part that I saw-- the size of my entire house.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And it had these wooden bunks that we've all seen so often in perhaps four or five layers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And in these bunks, on the floors, and scattered around the room were people dead, dying, getting ready to die, in a total-- total stupor.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Some dressed, some undressed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And the stench was just awful.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And this is the part of pictures that doesn't come through, because what you encounter in these places is the-- the stench of the dying who are defecating and urinating on themselves.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
